description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Scrub Nurse to join our dynamic theatre team at Kingston Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of the scrub team providing perioperative care to patients and rotate through a range of surgical specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Specialities covered are General Surgery, ENT and Maxilloacial Surgery, Breast Surgery, Upper GI, Colorectal, Urology, Gynae, Plastics, Elective &amp; Trauma Orthopaedics, Eyes, Paediatrics, Pain service and a 24-Hour Emergency Surgery Theatre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from qualified nurses and ODP’s with relevant experience looking for a new challenge, with the added opportunity for enhancement of clinical skills. Ideally you will have previous operating theatre experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department offers an excellent opportunity for staff to gain experience in all specialties. You must also be prepared to have a flexible approach to duties to meet the needs of this service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Main Theatre department comprises 8 operating theatres &amp; The Day Surgery Unit comprises of 4 theatres performing surgery in a variety of specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide you with support and training to develop new skills and continuous professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 21 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 09 December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal visit / more information about the post, please contact Jed Ablanque (Theatre Practice Educator)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;j.ablanque@nhs.net or call 020 8934 3073.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
